sql:
SELECT category_name, description, image_url 
FROM clothing_categories 
WHERE category_id = 0;

SELECT general_size, COUNT(*) AS number_of_entries
FROM sizing_data
GROUP BY general_size;

SELECT category_name
FROM clothing_categories
WHERE category_id > 10;

external_knowledge:
- "First category" refers to the category with category_id = 1; 
- "Sizes" refer to the unique sizing identifiers (sizing_id) associated with the products; 
- "Total quantity in stock" refers to the summed stock quantities for each unique size across all stores.
